title: ICE: BoundUniversalRegionError

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
### Code ```Rust use std::marker::PhantomData; use std::rc::Rc; pub fn func(f: F) -> A { A(B(C::new(D::new(move |st| f(st))))) } trait X {} trait Y { type V; } struct A(T); struct B(Rc); impl X for B {} struct C(T::V); impl C { fn new(_: T) -> Rc { todo!() } } struct D(F, PhantomData); impl D { fn new(_: F) -> Self { todo!() } } impl Y for D { type V = V; } ``` ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` rustc 1.68.0-nightly (0b90256ad 2023-01-13) binary: rustc commit-hash: 0b90256ada21c6a81b4c18f2c7a23151ab5fc232 commit-date: 2023-01-13 host: x86_64-pc-windows-msvc release: 1.68.0-nightly LLVM version: 15.0.6 ``` ### Error output ``` thread 'rustc' panicked at 'no entry found for key', compiler\rustc_borrowck\src\region_infer\mod.rs:2163:9 note: run with `RUST_BACKTRACE=1` environment variable to display a backtrace error: internal compiler error: unexpected panic note: the compiler unexpectedly panicked. this is a bug. note: we would appreciate a bug
